An Iranian military commander said Iraqitroops suffered 3,000 casualties in a week-old offensive byIran's forces in the mountains of northeast Iraq.    The Iranian news agency IRNA quoted the commander in theKurdish border village of Haj Omran as saying nine Iraqicounter-attacks had been repulsed with heavy casualties.    He said Iraq lost at least 3,000 men killed or wounded andanother 289 captured, IRNA, monitored by the BritishBroadcasting Corp, said.    Iran's offensive into Iraqi Kurdistan is coupled withsupport for anti-Iraqi Kurdish rebel operations in the region. REUTER&#3;